# childwaf allowlist – Example / Template
#
# Domains listed here will be explicitly allowed even if they appear in a
# blocklist category assigned to a child.
#
# HOW TO USE
# ──────────
# 1. Copy this file:  cp example.list kids-education.list
# 2. Add domains to allow.
# 3. Reference it in the child profile:
#      ALLOW_DOMAINS="khanacademy.org scratch.mit.edu"
#    (individual domains can also be listed directly in the child profile)
#
# NOTE: Allowlist enforcement via iptables ipsets is planned for a future
#       release. Currently, ALLOW_DOMAINS in child profiles is informational
#       and used only for dnsmasq server= directives (ensuring proper
#       resolution even when the domain is in a blocked category).
#
# Format: one domain per line; comments with #

# ── Educational ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# khanacademy.org
# scratch.mit.edu
# code.org
# duolingo.com
# brainpop.com

# ── School / homework ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# wikipedia.org
# wolframalpha.com

# ── Add your entries below ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
